==English==
====Etymology====
Latin '''[[praeveniens]]''', 'to come before'.
===Noun===

{{en-noun}}
#The act or condition of occuring earlier; being [[antecedent]]. Something done beforehand in anticipation of a later situation.

====Usage note====
The word and all its inflections and derivations occur nowhere else in contemporary English save the context of [[Methodism]] and the theology of [[w:John Wesley]]. See [[prevenient grace]].